In a medium #pot{}, bring @water{5%cups} to a boil, then reduce to a low simmer.

> You'll use it in Step 3.

Wash and dry produce. Halve, peel, and dice half the @yellow onion{1}(halved, peeled, and diced) (whole onion for 4). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens; mince greens. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and minced). Zest and quarter @lemon{1}(zested and quartered).

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium heat. Add diced onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened and lightly browned, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add @Italian chicken sausage mix{9%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings), scallion whites, garlic, and @arborio rice{3/4%cup}. Cook, stirring frequently, until garlic is fragrant and rice is translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with a big pinch of @salt{1/2%tsp} (we used ½ tsp; 1 tsp for 4).

Add 1 cup hot water and @chicken stock concentrate{2} to pan with rice mixture. Cook, stirring, until liquid has mostly absorbed. Repeat with remaining water—adding ½ cup at a time and stirring until liquid has mostly absorbed—until rice is al dente and mixture is creamy, ~{25-30%minutes}. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> Depending on the size of your pan, you may need a little more or a little less water.

While risotto cooks, finely chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}(finely chopped) (use leaves and thin stems; discard any thicker stems). Roughly chop @pistachios{1/2%ounce}(roughly chopped).

Once risotto is done, remove from heat; stir in ¾ of the @Italian cheese blend{1/2%cup}, half the parsley, half the scallion greens, @butter{2%tbsp} (4 TBSP for 4 servings), and a squeeze of lemon juice (juice from half the lemon for 4) until melted and combined.

> The risotto should be a little loose and saucy right before serving; it will thicken as it cools, so add more water if necessary.

Taste and season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide risotto between plates. Top with pistachios, remaining Italian cheese blend, remaining parsley, remaining scallion greens, and lemon zest to taste. Serve immediately with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Chicken Sausage is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.